            <div class="faq-item border border-surface-container rounded-xl"><button class="w-full flex justify-between items-center p-5 text-left" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><h3 class="font-bold text-primary text-sm pr-4">What's the difference between epoxy and cement grout?</h3><span class="material-symbols-outlined faq-chevron text-primary" aria-hidden="true">expand_more</span></button><div class="faq-answer px-5"><p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-relaxed pb-5">Epoxy grout is waterproof, stain-resistant, and never needs sealing &mdash; it lasts 15-20 years. Cement grout is cheaper but porous, requires sealing, and lasts 8-10 years. We recommend epoxy for showers because of constant water exposure.</p></div></div>

